\begin_layout Section*
Problem 1
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Today we model the cooling of a hot vertical aluminum plate with natural
 convection and radiation.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We will start with no radiation and a constant heat transfer coefficient
 and validate out model with an analytical solution.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Then we extend our model to include radiation heat transfer and solve the
 heat transfer coefficient from a correlation.
 Radiation makes the problem too complicated for analytical solution and
 we use measurement data for validation instead.
 The measurement data is included in file 
\shape italic
temperature.log
\shape default
 and was measured by the lecturers using open source tools and cheap electronics
 (
